1
00:00:05,030 --> 00:00:06,250
<i>[Class 3]</i>

2
00:00:06,250 --> 00:00:11,240
<i>In order to protect each other, the three of us...</i>

3
00:00:12,450 --> 00:00:14,700
<i>killed someone.</i>

4
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:16,700
<i>Let's go home together today.</i>

5
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:18,630
<i>I have to fight on my own.</i>

6
00:00:18,630 --> 00:00:20,350
<i>I don't want my fate to get the best of me.</i>

7
00:00:20,350 --> 00:00:22,960
<i>You knew what that old geezer was doing to me.</i>

8
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:25,130
<i>I'll kill you if you tell anyone.</i>

9
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:28,950
<i>Yuri...</i>

10
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:33,500
<i>I hear Satoko was the murderer.</i>

11
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:38,310
<i>He tried to attack me and, accidentally, I stabbed him.</i>

12
00:00:38,860 --> 00:00:43,080
<i>That day was the beginning of</i>

13
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:46,410
<i>a chain of murders.</i>

14
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:54,680
<i>I attended the same high school as them.</i>

15
00:00:56,090 --> 00:01:00,080
<i>Did Yuri know my identity?</i>

16
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:03,850
<i>Is that why she came to see me?</i>

17
00:01:05,490 --> 00:01:07,840
<i>Welcome. How many?</i>

18
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:10,670
Two. I'm meeting someone.

19
00:01:13,020 --> 00:01:19,990
<i>Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Influence Team @Viki.com</i>

20
00:01:24,970 --> 00:01:29,990
<i>[March, 2019]</i>

21
00:01:29,990 --> 00:01:33,930
May I ask you something before we get started?

22
00:01:33,930 --> 00:01:35,760
What is it?

23
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:41,210
Why did you write me the letter?

24
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:48,310
There are many writers who write about relationships between women.

25
00:01:49,370 --> 00:01:54,610
As I wrote in my letter, I'm your fan.

26
00:01:54,610 --> 00:01:56,750
Is that all?

27
00:01:57,330 --> 00:02:00,340
You have no other reason?

28
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:02,890
I don't.

29
00:02:02,890 --> 00:02:07,640
We are around the same age, so if I were to talk to anyone,

30
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:10,270
I wanted it to be you.

31
00:02:13,010 --> 00:02:16,270
Is anything wrong?

32
00:02:17,860 --> 00:02:19,510
No.

33
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:25,170
Please continue where we left off.

34
00:02:28,410 --> 00:02:35,060
You killed the man who attacked Maho at the park,

35
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:38,560
but it was Satoko who got arrested for it.

36
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:46,110
What happened to the three of you after that?

37
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:56,080
Satoko sacrificed herself for me.

38
00:02:56,970 --> 00:03:01,420
Neither Maho nor I knew why she did.

39
00:03:01,420 --> 00:03:03,560
Why did they arrest Satoko?
<i>[December, 1984]</i>

40
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:07,510
She turned herself in saying she killed him.

41
00:03:07,510 --> 00:03:09,080
Why...?

42
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:13,550
Satoko can see the park from her window.

43
00:03:14,140 --> 00:03:17,390
- Then...
- She might have been watching...

44
00:03:17,390 --> 00:03:19,550
when I killed that man.

45
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:21,860
Then, she is covering for you?

46
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:24,340
That's what I don't understand.

47
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:26,970
Satoko hates me, so she wouldn't cover for me.

48
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:29,040
But you two used to be friends, right?

49
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:32,180
Yeah, but not anymore.

50
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:39,170
Then... Satoko is telling the truth.

51
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:43,590
Satoko was alarmed when she saw it from her room and came out to the park.

52
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:45,820
But it was after we ran off.

53
00:03:45,820 --> 00:03:49,230
He was still alive and tried to attack Satoko then.

54
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:53,790
So, Satoko stabbed him to death.

55
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:59,690
But still...

56
00:03:59,690 --> 00:04:03,350
I'm going to the police.

57
00:04:03,350 --> 00:04:04,620
What?

58
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:07,390
I have to tell them that I stabbed him.

59
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:09,410
Absolutely not.

60
00:04:09,410 --> 00:04:14,270
I can't let you get arrested. It was my fault after all.

61
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:15,660
It wasn't your fault.

62
00:04:15,660 --> 00:04:18,400
And I don't want people to know.

63
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:23,760
You know how they talk about the girl who was attacked.

64
00:04:24,820 --> 00:04:30,220
What he said... How he touched me...

65
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:34,590
I don't want anyone to know. I would rather die than have people know about it.

66
00:04:38,690 --> 00:04:43,030
That man deserved to die.

67
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:49,220
If he had survived, I would still be scared to walk outside.

68
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,810
Please.

69
00:04:56,980 --> 00:05:00,730
Just let it go.

70
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:20,130
<i>I abandoned Satoko again.</i>

71
00:05:21,740 --> 00:05:26,440
<i>I killed someone to protect Maho,</i>

72
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:30,880
<i>and made Satoko pay for my sin.</i>

73
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:36,100
My action then

74
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:40,630
started the relationship the three of us had.

75
00:05:42,270 --> 00:05:44,090
And then...

76
00:05:45,330 --> 00:05:49,410
even after that...

77
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:56,890
we kept killing people.

78
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:10,030
<i>[INFLUENCE - Episode 2]</i>

79
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:13,280
- Good morning. Morning!
<i>- Good morning.</i>

80
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:16,150
- Morning.
<i>- Good morning.</i>

81
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:21,520
My parents said Satoko Hino might go to juvie.

82
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:25,590
But she was attacked. It was self-defense.

83
00:06:25,590 --> 00:06:29,480
She killed him, so I guess it was excessive defense.

84
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:33,490
To be honest, I can't sympathize with her, considering Rinako.

85
00:06:33,490 --> 00:06:36,180
I get it.

86
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:39,630
Okay, everyone.

87
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:42,510
Now, we are going to filet the jack mackerels to deep fry them.

88
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:44,110
Grab a knife, please.

89
00:06:44,110 --> 00:06:46,420
<i>Yes.</i>

90
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,230
What's wrong?

91
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,890
Nothing.

92
00:06:57,460 --> 00:06:59,360
How should I cut this?

93
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:02,930
I don't know. I've never done this before.

94
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:11,090
It's rubbery.

95
00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:14,170
Yuri?

96
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:16,690
Yuri! Are you okay? Teacher...

97
00:07:16,690 --> 00:07:19,490
- What's wrong?
- Yuri seems to be sick.

98
00:07:19,490 --> 00:07:22,050
Ms. Totsuka. Are you okay? What's wrong?

99
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:24,470
- Yuri?
- Ms. Totsuka.

100
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:34,890
Are you going to eat? You should have something.

101
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:38,830
Sorry. I don't want to.

102
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:42,420
Okay. I'll cut an apple later.

103
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,920
Mom.

104
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,600
Hm?

105
00:07:49,590 --> 00:07:51,220
It's nothing.

106
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:54,630
Get some sleep.

107
00:08:04,490 --> 00:08:06,290
What's wrong with Yuri?

108
00:08:06,290 --> 00:08:08,020
It was shocking for her.

109
00:08:08,020 --> 00:08:12,880
You know, Satoko being arrested.

110
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,260
We are shocked as well.

111
00:08:15,260 --> 00:08:18,620
Someone was murdered in our neighborhood.

112
00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:20,660
More beer.

113
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:24,520
I feel sorry for Satoko, but...

114
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:27,760
you can't say there was no fault on her part.

115
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:31,660
<i>Her mom says her parenting has nothing to do with it,</i>

116
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:35,100
<i>but it is the parent's responsibility.</i>

117
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:39,950
<i>She left Satoko until she got that way.</i>

118
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:44,190
<i>Is our neighbor delivering a community circular? Coming!</i>

119
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:46,460
Don't talk too long at the door.

120
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:48,920
Okay, okay.

121
00:09:01,930 --> 00:09:04,890
<i>Yuri. I'm coming in.</i>

122
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:12,530
Well, detectives want to talk to you.

123
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:14,190
Come on in.

124
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:19,600
You are Yuri Totsuka, right?

125
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:23,160
We are investigating the murder case that took place in the park the other day.

126
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:25,390
Can we talk to you for a bit?

127
00:09:25,390 --> 00:09:27,690
What is it? What does she have to do with it?

128
00:09:27,690 --> 00:09:29,370
Where were you on the night of the murder?

129
00:09:29,370 --> 00:09:32,760
She was at home. She would never go out at night.

130
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:36,430
Mrs. Totsuka, we would like your daughter to answer.

131
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:42,530
The estimated time of the victim's death is between 10:30 p.m. and 12:00 a.m.

132
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:45,400
Were you at home during that time?

133
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:48,890
A little after 10:00,

134
00:09:48,890 --> 00:09:53,090
I went out to see my friend off.

135
00:09:53,090 --> 00:09:56,190
What are you investigating? You've already arrested the perpetrator.

136
00:09:56,190 --> 00:09:59,530
Actually, the knife that was used as a weapon

137
00:09:59,530 --> 00:10:02,400
had fingerprints that belong to someone else.

138
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,630
What?

139
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:06,190
On the night of the murder, someone saw a girl

140
00:10:06,190 --> 00:10:08,790
washing her hands near the park.

141
00:10:08,790 --> 00:10:11,120
- What are you talking about?
- Yuri.

142
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:13,910
You killed him, right?

143
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:18,830
You stabbed this man to death and framed Satoko Hino.

144
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:33,790
<i>I know. I heard about that.</i>

145
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:36,340
I was really shocked when I heard it.

146
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:40,100
Her husband may look conservative, but he's bold.

147
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,130
We can't judge a person by the appearance.

148
00:10:42,130 --> 00:10:44,880
Why don't you invite her in? It's cold.

149
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:47,750
- Oh my, he's mad.
- Take a look at this, okay?

150
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,730
<i>Sure. Thanks for delivering it.</i>

151
00:10:49,730 --> 00:10:51,930
- Let's talk more tomorrow.
<i>- Sure thing.</i>

152
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:07,170
- I'll do it today for sure.
- Sounds great.

153
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:42,220
<i>[Asano Kouen Mae Police Station]</i>

154
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:52,690
Why did you leave alone? We promised to go back together.

155
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:55,870
Sorry.

156
00:12:25,620 --> 00:12:30,870
Were you going to turn yourself into the police earlier?

157
00:12:33,410 --> 00:12:37,240
- I'm not sure...
- I asked you not to.

158
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:44,210
Do you value your friendship with Satoko more than me?

159
00:12:45,350 --> 00:12:47,220
That's not it.

160
00:12:49,850 --> 00:12:51,660
It's not, but...

161
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:58,390
We shouldn't stay together.

162
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:06,420
Because I'm no longer an ordinary girl.

163
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:08,130
Me, either.

164
00:13:08,130 --> 00:13:10,610
We're not the same.

165
00:13:10,610 --> 00:13:13,080
You're a victim.

166
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:16,140
- But, I...
- We're in the same boat.

167
00:13:19,830 --> 00:13:22,430
You and I are not.

168
00:13:25,650 --> 00:13:27,760
<i>I'm back.</i>

169
00:13:28,810 --> 00:13:32,400
<i>Maho, are you there?</i>

170
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:36,600
Welcome back. You're back so early.

171
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:40,450
I was in the neighborhood for business, so I came straight home.

172
00:13:40,450 --> 00:13:42,180
Your friend?

173
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:45,570
I'm Totsuka. Nice to meet you.

174
00:13:45,570 --> 00:13:47,120
Oh...

175
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:51,520
- Yuri Totsuka?
- Yes.

176
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:54,780
Mom, we're about to study.

177
00:13:54,780 --> 00:13:58,720
Studying with your friend doesn't benefit your academic performance.

178
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:04,470
- Your parents don't teach you that at home, Ms. Totsuka?
- Mom.

179
00:14:04,470 --> 00:14:08,830
Since Maho enrolled in high school with a low academic performance,

180
00:14:08,830 --> 00:14:11,460
I'm thinking of sending her to a cram school.

181
00:14:11,460 --> 00:14:15,170
So she won't have much time to hang out with you.

182
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:17,170
Mom...

183
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:21,640
<i>What are you saying? Don't be rude.</i>

184
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:25,850
<i>I told you not to hang out with her.</i>

185
00:14:25,850 --> 00:14:29,830
She grew up with Satoko Hino who murdered a man.

186
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:33,570
- It has nothing to do with Yuri.
- Of course, it does.

187
00:14:33,570 --> 00:14:38,030
A person's life is determined by upbringing and the environment one was raised.

188
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:39,960
<i>[Moegi Insurance Information]</i>

189
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,290
You should choose your friends wisely.

190
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:44,530
She is not on the same level as you.

191
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:47,170
Stop it already.

192
00:14:48,180 --> 00:14:52,340
Right after that, I gave up being friends with her.

193
00:14:53,290 --> 00:14:55,270
Gave up?

194
00:14:57,090 --> 00:15:01,670
I knew how grown-ups can be unreasonable sometimes.

195
00:15:03,930 --> 00:15:07,070
I remember, a long ago...

196
00:15:07,070 --> 00:15:10,370
my parents refused to help Satoko

197
00:15:11,030 --> 00:15:13,690
who was sexually abused.

198
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:20,440
Just like that, Maho's mother excluded me

199
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,920
from Maho's life.

200
00:15:24,030 --> 00:15:28,690
I bet Maho didn't agree to that.

201
00:15:28,690 --> 00:15:33,770
She doesn't seem to be the type to abandon her friend just because her mom said so.

202
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:37,520
You're right.

203
00:15:39,020 --> 00:15:44,120
But I was the one who drove her away.

204
00:15:57,510 --> 00:16:03,280
Gradually, the distance between us became greater.

205
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:06,820
Because of the incident,

206
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:11,880
our friendship turned completely sour.

207
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:14,330
- Good morning.
- Morning.
<i>[January 1986]</i>

208
00:16:14,330 --> 00:16:16,380
- Good morning.
- Good morning!

209
00:16:16,380 --> 00:16:18,630
<i>[11th Grade, Class 3]</i>

210
00:16:26,190 --> 00:16:29,070
Was she released from juvie already?

211
00:16:29,070 --> 00:16:31,380
I can't stand being in the same class with her.

212
00:16:31,380 --> 00:16:32,830
- Let's go.
- Okay.

213
00:16:32,830 --> 00:16:34,620
How absurd.

214
00:16:44,850 --> 00:16:49,250
Yuri, long time no see.

215
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:51,230
I missed you.

216
00:16:51,230 --> 00:16:54,220
I'm glad that we're in the same class.

217
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:07,410
"Thanks" would be nice.

218
00:17:07,410 --> 00:17:10,430
Your friend is ungrateful.

219
00:17:10,430 --> 00:17:14,240
Satoko, let me ask you something.

220
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:23,890
I'm out unexpectedly fast, aren't I?

221
00:17:23,890 --> 00:17:25,460
What?

222
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:27,850
Getting released from juvie.

223
00:17:29,050 --> 00:17:32,400
It is? I don't know much about it.

224
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:35,820
The police discovered many items in his car.

225
00:17:35,820 --> 00:17:38,020
Packing tape and handcuffs.

226
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:42,120
Those items speak of his ill intention itself.

227
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:46,040
So they reduced my sentence under the circumstance.

228
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:53,940
Satoko, did you confess to the police the truth?

229
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:55,830
I did.

230
00:17:57,350 --> 00:18:01,570
But... that man...

231
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:13,350
I know you stabbed him with a knife.

232
00:18:15,270 --> 00:18:18,540
When I was looking out my window that night,

233
00:18:18,540 --> 00:18:21,070
I saw the man attacking Maho.

234
00:18:21,070 --> 00:18:23,760
Let go of me.

235
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:40,140
Let's leave. It's self-defense.

236
00:18:41,270 --> 00:18:44,260
Yuri, go back home.

237
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:04,100
Those girls...

238
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:31,180
Just now...

239
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:34,870
I killed a person.

240
00:19:39,850 --> 00:19:42,270
Why...?

241
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:45,340
Why did you kill him?

242
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:47,570
I wanted to protect you, Yuri.

243
00:19:49,220 --> 00:19:53,020
If I let him live, he would have exposed you.

244
00:19:53,540 --> 00:19:56,620
I killed him to shut him up.

245
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:02,840
Did you believe that?

246
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:07,950
When I saw you stabbing the man,

247
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:13,840
I was envious of you because you might be getting arrested.

248
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:19,450
You can escape

249
00:20:19,450 --> 00:20:23,800
from home, school, and reality.

250
00:20:27,330 --> 00:20:32,760
Don't tell me... is your grandpa

251
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,730
still molesting you?

252
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:39,250
Is that what you wanted to escape from?

253
00:20:43,580 --> 00:20:45,710
Yuri...

254
00:20:46,630 --> 00:20:50,840
you've neglected me, yet you helped Maho.

255
00:20:51,990 --> 00:20:53,250
Sorry.

256
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:55,350
I'm sorry, Satoko.

257
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:03,190
Can you help me this time?

258
00:21:05,210 --> 00:21:07,500
Kill that old geezer for me.

259
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:15,700
If I were to kill him, the police would suspect me first. So you do it.

260
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:20,620
Don't you get it?

261
00:21:20,620 --> 00:21:24,960
You were free because I took the blame for you.

262
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,660
Although it was self-defense,

263
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:32,350
you know how the public condemns a person who has been involved in a crime, don't you?

264
00:21:38,740 --> 00:21:41,280
It's your turn now, Yuri.

265
00:21:44,370 --> 00:21:49,140
<i>Is there an end to the chain of the murders?</i>

266
00:21:54,850 --> 00:21:59,040
<i>What am I getting myself into?</i>

267
00:22:01,510 --> 00:22:03,650
<i>More importantly...</i>

268
00:22:03,650 --> 00:22:10,020
<i>Is Yuri Totsuka telling me the truth?</i>

269
00:22:11,650 --> 00:22:14,020
- Guys, don't run.
- Bye, Teacher.

270
00:22:14,020 --> 00:22:15,850
Be safe.

271
00:22:17,370 --> 00:22:19,920
You want to know the incident that happened in the past?

272
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:23,180
Right. But I bet you wouldn't know.

273
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:25,790
Since it's happened more than 30 years ago.

274
00:22:25,790 --> 00:22:29,320
I remember the incident and you.

275
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:32,160
Aren't you Tomomi Oikawa?

276
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:35,000
I'm Naoko Okao. We were in the same grade.

277
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,030
We've never been in the same class or anything.

278
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:41,120
Seriously? I'm sorry, but I didn't know.

279
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:43,830
- You became a novelist, right?
- Yes.

280
00:22:43,830 --> 00:22:45,720
Are you collecting materials for your book?

281
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:48,460
Well, sort of.

282
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:50,840
I remember Yuri, too.

283
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:53,150
I've been in the same class as her.

284
00:22:53,150 --> 00:22:55,670
Remember the incident?

285
00:22:55,670 --> 00:23:00,190
When Satoko Hino was attacked at a park near her house.

286
00:23:00,190 --> 00:23:02,190
<i>- Bye, Teacher.</i>
- Be safe, girls.

287
00:23:02,190 --> 00:23:03,930
<i>We will.</i>

288
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:07,830
The incident she ended up stabbing a man to death?

289
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:10,500
Do you know anything about the case?

290
00:23:10,500 --> 00:23:12,920
For instance, she killed the man

291
00:23:12,920 --> 00:23:16,520
in order to protect someone.

292
00:23:16,560 --> 00:23:19,620
I didn't know there was such a rumor.

293
00:23:19,620 --> 00:23:22,620
It's hypothetically speaking.

294
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:30,570
Hard to imagine Satoko would have sacrificed herself for someone.

295
00:23:30,570 --> 00:23:34,980
We had no doubt that she killed him.

296
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:38,330
It's only natural based on her outrageous behaviors.

297
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:53,930
Do you know the whereabouts of Satoko and Maho?

298
00:23:53,930 --> 00:23:56,860
I'm sorry. I don't.

299
00:23:57,720 --> 00:24:00,750
They all lived in the same apartment complex, right?

300
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:03,160
An apartment complex?

301
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:07,560
Right. I remember Satoko moved out.

302
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:10,950
About half a year after, she was released from juvie.

303
00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:13,910
When Satoko's grandfather passed away.

304
00:24:14,970 --> 00:24:16,820
Her grandfather?

305
00:24:28,070 --> 00:24:31,580
Let's wait another six months to kill the old geezer.

306
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:36,330
During the summer break?

307
00:24:36,330 --> 00:24:40,500
Until then, we won't speak alone in public.

308
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:43,660
We can't let others suspect that we're partners in crime.

309
00:24:52,410 --> 00:24:53,790
I agree.

310
00:24:53,790 --> 00:24:55,430
Yuri, did you study?

311
00:24:55,430 --> 00:24:57,700
Sort of.

312
00:24:57,700 --> 00:24:59,870
Naoko, can you guess the questions of the exam?

313
00:24:59,870 --> 00:25:03,250
I'm sure Teacher Sato would include this on the test.

314
00:25:03,250 --> 00:25:09,150
Also... the grammar. What else did he say?

315
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:16,100
Don't worry.

316
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:21,560
We were never seen as friends, so nobody will suspect you, Yuri.

317
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:25,520
You have no motive to kill my grandpa.

318
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:29,450
I know, but we have to think of an untraceable method.

319
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:34,840
We should stage an accident.

320
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:38,740
Falling down the stairs, or getting hit by a car.

321
00:25:38,740 --> 00:25:41,030
Falling down the stairs won't kill him.

322
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:45,710
Someone might see me when I push him to a car.

323
00:25:46,290 --> 00:25:49,430
How about a robbery?

324
00:25:49,430 --> 00:25:54,180
When he is alone, sneak into the house and stab him with a knife.

325
00:25:54,180 --> 00:25:56,370
Isn't that your forte, Yuri?

326
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:02,280
It's a joke.

327
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:14,050
I'll push him out a window.

328
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:18,290
Your apartment is on the fifth floor.

329
00:26:18,290 --> 00:26:21,220
I'm sure he can't survive when falling from that height.

330
00:26:22,190 --> 00:26:23,770
Prepare a spare key for me.

331
00:26:23,770 --> 00:26:27,240
I'll lock the door when I'm done.

332
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:29,630
The police will handle the case as an accident.

333
00:26:32,350 --> 00:26:34,510
But if you visit the house out of the blue,

334
00:26:34,510 --> 00:26:36,930
he might suspect something.

335
00:26:37,820 --> 00:26:39,440
When you leave the house,

336
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:42,060
tell him I'm stopping by

337
00:26:42,060 --> 00:26:44,570
and I'll be waiting for you at your house.

338
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:52,150
What's the matter? You seem so enthusiastic, suddenly.

339
00:26:55,630 --> 00:26:57,850
You want him dead, do you not?

340
00:26:58,340 --> 00:27:00,610
Or were you bluffing?

341
00:27:09,930 --> 00:27:11,150
<i>[Window]</i>

342
00:27:11,150 --> 00:27:13,950
Which room does he normally stay in?

343
00:27:13,950 --> 00:27:16,100
This room.

344
00:27:16,100 --> 00:27:19,620
He sleeps in the room with me and my little brother.

345
00:27:19,620 --> 00:27:22,160
It's crazy, right?

346
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:27,470
My brother and I sleep in a bunk bed, and my grandpa sleeps on the floor.

347
00:27:27,470 --> 00:27:31,450
He crawls into my bed even now, pretending to be half asleep.

348
00:27:34,380 --> 00:27:37,070
Why didn't you tell your mom about him?

349
00:27:39,410 --> 00:27:42,610
My mom pays no attention to me.

350
00:27:42,610 --> 00:27:45,420
She adores my little brother, though.

351
00:27:49,890 --> 00:27:51,580
Yuri...

352
00:27:52,850 --> 00:27:54,820
Thank you.

353
00:27:56,490 --> 00:27:58,910
It's too early to thank me.

354
00:27:58,910 --> 00:28:01,270
I believe in you.

355
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:05,970
I was stunned

356
00:28:05,970 --> 00:28:08,320
when you stabbed the man.

357
00:28:10,590 --> 00:28:14,920
I stabbed the old geezer to death repeatedly in my head.

358
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:17,460
But I could never have translated the thought into action.

359
00:28:22,850 --> 00:28:24,620
You know...

360
00:28:24,620 --> 00:28:27,650
we used to play together here.

361
00:28:42,070 --> 00:28:44,650
Yuri, come here.

362
00:28:47,870 --> 00:28:49,990
Yuri!

363
00:29:16,780 --> 00:29:18,860
Don't.

364
00:29:18,860 --> 00:29:22,580
That was close. Get wet.

365
00:29:26,430 --> 00:29:29,040
Stop it. I'll push you, too.

366
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,040
Don't do that.

367
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,320
<i>Let's go, Satoko.</i>

368
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:39,520
<i>Closer to the water.</i>

369
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:13,140
After he's dead, we shouldn't see each other.

370
00:30:14,670 --> 00:30:18,300
Right. I agree.

371
00:30:19,190 --> 00:30:22,170
The statute of limitations for murder is 15 years.

372
00:30:22,170 --> 00:30:25,130
So, we can see each other again after 15 years.

373
00:30:29,370 --> 00:30:35,380
Hey, did you watch the show "The Life of Nomads" on TV last night?

374
00:30:35,380 --> 00:30:38,390
Nomads? From where?

375
00:30:38,390 --> 00:30:41,530
I don't know. Somewhere in the Soviet Union.

376
00:30:43,770 --> 00:30:48,620
In 15 years, let's go there together.

377
00:30:49,210 --> 00:30:55,190
We become nomads. We walk around looking for weeds to feed the sheep.

378
00:30:56,210 --> 00:30:59,510
Sure. Sounds good.

379
00:31:16,510 --> 00:31:18,150
Ah...

380
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:30,970
He's out.

381
00:31:37,780 --> 00:31:39,950
Don't.

382
00:31:39,950 --> 00:31:44,490
You think you need him so no one can mess with you, right?

383
00:31:44,490 --> 00:31:46,430
Forget it.

384
00:31:46,430 --> 00:31:48,860
I'm going to protect you from now on.

385
00:31:50,220 --> 00:31:52,570
That's not all.

386
00:31:54,980 --> 00:31:58,150
He is the same as me.

387
00:31:58,150 --> 00:32:00,270
He was lonely.

388
00:32:05,670 --> 00:32:11,420
His parents got divorced when he was little, and he was raised by his mother,

389
00:32:11,420 --> 00:32:15,680
but she was always away flirting with men.

390
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:20,630
She only came back home once in a while to give him money.

391
00:32:20,630 --> 00:32:24,140
She didn't care about her child at all.

392
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:31,540
That's why...

393
00:32:31,540 --> 00:32:33,790
we stayed together.

394
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:52,970
When did you come out?

395
00:32:52,970 --> 00:32:54,960
Yesterday.

396
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:57,510
I was waiting for your call.

397
00:32:57,510 --> 00:33:03,630
Well, I didn't want to bother you when you might be seeing someone else.

398
00:33:03,630 --> 00:33:06,080
Why would I?

399
00:33:07,340 --> 00:33:09,930
I was in juvie, too.

400
00:33:09,930 --> 00:33:11,560
What?

401
00:33:13,770 --> 00:33:19,610
Nothing is going to change between us.

402
00:33:36,630 --> 00:33:41,210
<i>Maybe he was the victim of society.</i>

403
00:33:41,210 --> 00:33:43,800
<i>That boy, Ogata.</i>

404
00:33:45,470 --> 00:33:47,760
His parents abandoned him

405
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:52,210
and nobody helped him while he was rotting away.

406
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:58,970
It's just like nobody helped Satoko Hino

407
00:33:58,970 --> 00:34:01,980
when she was molested by her grandfather.

408
00:34:06,410 --> 00:34:09,240
You may be right.

409
00:34:10,170 --> 00:34:13,000
At the time,

410
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,780
I couldn't think that far, though.

411
00:34:18,250 --> 00:34:23,750
Anyway, Satoko and I

412
00:34:23,750 --> 00:34:28,400
put together a plan for summer break.

413
00:34:30,750 --> 00:34:35,560
What about Maho? What was she doing?

414
00:34:36,540 --> 00:34:41,060
I wasn't talking to Maho at all by then.

415
00:34:41,060 --> 00:34:42,640
I think the outfit would suit you, Maho.

416
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:45,910
- Really?
- You'll definitely look cute

417
00:34:45,910 --> 00:34:49,470
This denim jacket will look good on you, Sayaka.

418
00:34:49,470 --> 00:34:52,960
- Yeah, it's cute. Let's go shopping on Sunday.
- Sounds good.

419
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:55,540
- Can you go, Maho?
- Yeah.

420
00:34:55,540 --> 00:34:58,250
<i>[July, 1986]</i>

421
00:34:58,250 --> 00:35:00,720
<i>[Reminder for Summer Break]</i>

422
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:03,960
- See you!
- Bye!

423
00:35:07,930 --> 00:35:12,920
I'm going to the dentist for an alibi tomorrow, as planned.

424
00:35:19,010 --> 00:35:21,690
- Thank you for the food.
- Yeah.

425
00:35:21,690 --> 00:35:25,690
You didn't finish it. Are you unwell?

426
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:27,380
I'm fine.

427
00:35:30,370 --> 00:35:32,990
I'm going to the bookstore.

428
00:35:39,030 --> 00:35:41,100
Be careful.

429
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:41,040
<i>[506, Hino]</i>

430
00:36:48,770 --> 00:36:50,580
Who are you?

431
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:52,560
I'm a friend of Satoko's.

432
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:54,570
Satoko went to the dentist.

433
00:36:54,570 --> 00:36:58,920
Ah, she told me to wait in her room.

434
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:01,270
In her room?

435
00:37:01,270 --> 00:37:04,790
Yes. Can I come in?

436
00:37:08,330 --> 00:37:10,970
I remember she told me about it.

437
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:22,710
Geez, how dare she ask an old man to answer the door for her.

438
00:37:28,340 --> 00:37:31,270
Do you live around here?

439
00:37:31,270 --> 00:37:32,830
No.

440
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:36,460
Why do you ask?

441
00:37:37,860 --> 00:37:42,260
This is the first time Satoko has invited her friend.

442
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:47,200
You look like a decent girl. What do you want from her?

443
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:50,490
I'm here just to hang out with her.

444
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:55,360
I'm going to wait in her room.

445
00:38:10,660 --> 00:38:15,950
<i>My brother and I sleep in a bunk bed, and my grandpa sleeps on the floor.</i>

446
00:38:15,950 --> 00:38:19,940
<i>He crawls into my bed even now, pretending to be half asleep.</i>

447
00:38:21,250 --> 00:38:23,770
It's messy, right?

448
00:38:23,770 --> 00:38:27,980
Satoko is really sloppy.

449
00:38:27,980 --> 00:38:31,260
She won't grow up to be a decent woman.

450
00:38:31,260 --> 00:38:34,710
Are you okay to leave the laundry out?

451
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:36,250
What?

452
00:38:36,250 --> 00:38:38,810
It's supposed to rain in the evening.

453
00:38:39,350 --> 00:38:41,170
Rain?

454
00:38:44,410 --> 00:38:46,390
The forecast said so.

455
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:52,890
Really?

456
00:39:10,450 --> 00:39:12,460
Oh, well.

457
00:39:12,460 --> 00:39:14,530
How do I get it off?

458
00:39:14,530 --> 00:39:17,360
What, it's stuck.

459
00:39:23,450 --> 00:39:25,060
<i>Yuri...</i>

460
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:28,340
<i>Thank you.</i>

461
00:39:33,530 --> 00:39:35,120
I got it.

462
00:39:35,810 --> 00:39:37,410
What?

463
00:39:38,330 --> 00:39:41,010
I'll take the laundry.

464
00:39:41,010 --> 00:39:42,990
Ah, thanks.

465
00:39:43,630 --> 00:39:45,470
I'm going to go and get the one I dropped.

466
00:39:54,680 --> 00:39:57,910
- Hey, Yuri.
- I'll do it right the next time.

467
00:39:57,910 --> 00:40:01,800
He doesn't suspect a thing, so I'm sure I can do it.

468
00:40:09,270 --> 00:40:11,790
Failing to do it the first time

469
00:40:11,790 --> 00:40:16,620
erased my fear, actually.

470
00:40:18,930 --> 00:40:23,980
I could use the same method only once more.

471
00:40:24,890 --> 00:40:30,040
So, I was preparing myself

472
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:32,710
and waiting for the next opportunity.

473
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:43,980
It was then that Maho called me to her place.

474
00:40:46,330 --> 00:40:48,020
Where is your mom today?

475
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:49,850
She has a meeting in Tokyo.

476
00:40:49,850 --> 00:40:52,520
She's not coming back anytime soon, so don't worry.

477
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:03,830
Welcome.

478
00:41:05,710 --> 00:41:07,180
Why?

479
00:41:07,180 --> 00:41:11,430
Yuri, is it true that you are going to kill her grandfather?

480
00:41:12,210 --> 00:41:16,500
I told her because you were getting cold feet.

481
00:41:16,500 --> 00:41:19,790
I asked her to testify to the police if you ran away.

482
00:41:19,790 --> 00:41:21,770
Testify?

483
00:41:25,940 --> 00:41:29,080
That you are the one who stabbed that man first.

484
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:30,930
I haven't agreed to it.

485
00:41:30,930 --> 00:41:32,980
That's why I called you here.

486
00:41:32,980 --> 00:41:36,450
She took the blame for you on her own, to begin with.

487
00:41:36,450 --> 00:41:38,550
You don't need to feel responsible for it.

488
00:41:38,550 --> 00:41:40,160
Don't make me laugh.

489
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:42,660
You are the reason all that happened because you were attacked.

490
00:41:42,660 --> 00:41:46,610
You took the blame so you could use Yuri later, didn't you?

491
00:41:46,610 --> 00:41:48,860
That's enough.

492
00:41:48,860 --> 00:41:51,240
I'm not going to run away.

493
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:53,480
So, you don't need to ask Maho to do that.

494
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:54,500
Yuri.

495
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:56,620
So, leave now.

496
00:41:58,420 --> 00:42:01,610
Just pray that Yuri is not going to run away.

497
00:42:01,610 --> 00:42:05,330
It is the fact that she stabbed that man.

498
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:08,670
I will make you testify.

499
00:42:23,210 --> 00:42:26,060
I'll make sure you won't get involved in this.

500
00:42:26,060 --> 00:42:28,160
I'm going to kill him.

501
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:31,740
What are you saying? I'm not testifying.

502
00:42:31,740 --> 00:42:35,330
Even if you run away, I will never tell them that you stabbed him.

503
00:42:36,190 --> 00:42:38,520
So, don't listen to her.

504
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:42,720
Or else, I'm going to tell Satoko's parents about your plan.

505
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:46,560
Did Satoko tell you

506
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:48,760
why she wants her grandfather killed?

507
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:51,930
No.

508
00:42:51,930 --> 00:42:53,930
I don't want to know.

509
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:02,490
The man I stabbed...

510
00:43:03,640 --> 00:43:06,130
What he attempted to do to you,

511
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:10,110
her grandfather was doing to her exactly that.

512
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:13,510
And it's been going on since she was little.

513
00:43:15,980 --> 00:43:18,840
I knew about it,

514
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:21,190
but I couldn't save her.

515
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:29,000
Iâ€™ve forsaken Satoko in a living hell.

516
00:43:35,450 --> 00:43:37,090
Maho,

517
00:43:38,940 --> 00:43:41,470
grown-ups are unreliable.

518
00:43:42,340 --> 00:43:44,990
Nobody is going to help us.

519
00:43:47,390 --> 00:43:49,980
I remember you said,

520
00:43:49,980 --> 00:43:53,020
your mother is too occupied with her personal matters,

521
00:43:53,020 --> 00:43:56,050
so you have to fight on your own.

522
00:44:00,370 --> 00:44:05,920
It's time for me to fight for Satoko's sake now.

523
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:10,950
I'll help you.

524
00:44:12,720 --> 00:44:16,510
